text: Queen Anne can mean: * Anne, Queen of Great Britain (1665–1714), queen of England, Scotland and Ireland (1702–1707) and of Great Britain (1707–1714) **Queen Anne style architecture, an architectural style from her reign, and its revivals **Queen Anne style furniture **Queen Anne (play), a 2015 play on Anne's life **Queen Anne's War during her reign **MS Queen Anne Ship named after the Monarch ==Other queens called Anne, Ann or Anna== *Anna Jagiellon (1523–1596), queen of Poland *Anna Pavlovna of Russia (1795–1865), queen of the Netherlands *Anne Boleyn (1501/7–1536), queen of England *Anne Neville (1456–1485), queen of England *Anne of Austria, Queen of Poland (1573–1598), queen of Poland and Sweden *Anne of Austria (1601–1666), queen of France *Anne of Bohemia (1290–1313), queen of Bohemia *Anne of Bohemia and Hungary (1503–1547), queen of Hungary, Germany and Bohemia *Anne of Bohemia (1366–1394), queen of England *Anne of Brittany (1477–1514), queen of France *Anne of Cleves (1515–1557), queen of England *Anna of Austria, Queen of Spain (1549-1580) *Anne of Denmark (1574–1619), queen of Scotland and England *Anne of Foix-Candale (1484–1506), queen of Hungary and Bohemia *Anne of Kiev (c. 1024–1075), queen of France *Queen Ann (Pamunkey chief) (c. 1650–c. 1725), Native American tribal leader in colonial Virginia *Queen Anne of Romania (1923–2016) *Queen Anna of Arendelle, a name given to Anna at the end of the 2019 Disney film Frozen II ==Places== *Queen Anne, Maryland, on Maryland's Eastern Shore *Queen Anne, Prince George's County, Maryland, census-designated place on the Patuxent River *Queen Anne's County, Maryland *Queen Anne, Seattle, Washington ==Related pages== *Queen Anne-Marie of Greece (born 1946), queen of Greece
